'''''How the World Sees America''''' is a [[video blog]] run by global correspondent [[Amar C. Bakshi]] and sponsored by ''[[The Washington Post]]'' and [[Newsweek Magazine]]. It features daily articles, which include text and short video clips, about citizens around the world impacted by the [[United States]] politically, economically and culturally.<ref>{{Citation|title=Anti-American Ambivalence|url=http://www.wnyc.org/story/129968-anti-american-ambivalence?tab=transcript|language=en|accessdate=2017-11-21}}</ref>
==History== The project launched on May 15, 2007 in England, and wrapped up in Mexico in March 2008.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=88908339|title=Blogger Researches 'How the World Sees America'|work=NPR.org|access-date=2017-11-21|language=en}}</ref>
