==Management== The Kimbell Art Museum derives around 65% of its $12m budget from its unrestricted endowment of more than $400 million.<ref>Christopher Knight (March 11, 2012), [http://articles.latimes.com/2012/mar/11/entertainment/la-ca-knight-potts-notebook-20120311 Critic's Notebook: Timothy Potts' past and future] ''[[Los Angeles Times]]''.</ref> The endowment fell from $466m to $398m during the first years of the [[2007–2012 global financial crisis]].<ref>Jason Edward Kaufman (January 8, 2009), [http://www.theartnewspaper.com/articles/How-the-richest-US-museums-are-weathering-the-storm/16705 How the richest US museums are weathering the storm] ''[[The Art Newspaper]]''.</ref> The museum has no special funds for acquisitions.<ref>Judith H. Dobrzynski (March 14, 2012), [https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/15/arts/artsspecial/a-fund-for-buying-art-burnishes-collections-and-reputations.html How an Acquisition Fund Burnishes Reputations] ''[[New York Times]]''.</ref> Museum membership is at 15,000.
