{{Infobox University |name = Nordic Institute of Asian Studies |native_name = Nordisk Institut for Asien Studier |latin_name = |image = |motto = |established = 1968 |type = University institute |endowment = |staff = |faculty = [[University of Copenhagen Faculty of Social Sciences]] |dean = |chairman = Geir Helgesen (Norway) |students = |undergrad = |postgrad = |doctoral = |city = [[Copenhagen]] |state = |country = [[Denmark]] |campus = [[City Campus (University of Copenhagen)|City Campus]] |affiliations = [[Nordic Centre in Shanghai]] |website = [http://www.nias.ku.dk/ NIAS] }} '''Nordic Institute of Asian Studies''' ({{lang-da|Nordisk Institut for Asien Studier}}), or '''NIAS''' for short, is a university Institute for [[Asian studies]] of [[Copenhagen University]] in Denmark. The institute is located in Copenhagen and serve all five [[Nordic countries]], comprising Denmark (including Greenland and Faroe Islands), Norway, Sweden, Finland and Iceland.
NIAS was established under the auspices of the [[Nordic Council of Ministers]] in 1968 as a Nordic focal point for research on Asia.<ref name=History>{{cite web|url=http://nias.ku.dk/about-nias/history |title=History |publisher=NIAS |website=www.nias.ku.dk |accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref>
== Structure and purpose == {{expand section|date=February 2017}} On 1 January 2005, NIAS was incorporated as an independent academic institute under Danish University Law and is now a centre under the Department of Political Science of the University of Copenhagen.<ref name=History/> The Department of Political Science has administrative and legal responsibility for NIAS. The independence of the institute is manifested through NIAS own strategy and research policy.
== Library == Nordic Institute of Asian Studies holds its own library, NIAS Library and Information Centre (NIAS LINC), serving the NIAS community. NIAS LINC has been a [[digital library]] since 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nias.ku.dk/nias-library |title=NIAS Library |publisher=NIAS |website=www.nias.ku.dk |accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref>
== Publication == Nordic Institute of Asian Studies operate its own press, NIAS Press, focusing primarily on social sciences and history relating to contemporary [[Southeast Asia]] and [[East Asia]], but not exclusively. NIAS Press presents authors from all over the world and publishes exclusively in English.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nias.ku.dk/nias-press |title=NIAS Press |publisher=NIAS |website=www.nias.ku.dk |accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref>
"Asia in Focus" is a peer-reviewed academic journal published twice a year on-line by NIAS.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asiainfocus.dk/about/ |title=Asia in Focus |accessdate=21 November 2016}}</ref>
